    "plan_content": "Here's the full plan for the **Stepper** compound component. Everything has been researched and designed — no existing files will be touched except to add registry entries.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n### 4 files total\n\n| Action | File |\n|---|---|\n| **Create** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` |\n| **Create** | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` |\n| **Edit** (entry only) | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` |\n| **Edit** (entry only) | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` |\n\n### Component architecture\n\nNo Radix UI primitive exists for steppers, so the component uses **two-level React context**:\n- **`StepperContext`** (root) — holds `value`, `onValueChange`, `orientation`\n- **`StepperItemContext`** (per-item) — holds `step`, `isActive`, `isCompleted`\n\n**7 exported sub-components**: `Stepper`, `StepperItem`, `StepperTrigger`, `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent`\n\n### Key design choices\n- **Orientation** propagates via CSS `group-data-[orientation=...]/stepper:` selectors (no prop drilling) — identical to how `tabs.tsx` works\n- **`StepperTrigger`** has a built-in circular indicator (number or ✓ checkmark) — mirrors how `AccordionTrigger` has a built-in chevron\n- **`StepperContent`** shows/hides via `data-[state=inactive]:hidden` — same pattern as Accordion/Tabs\n- **`isCompleted`** = `completed prop || value > step` — supports both explicit prop control and auto linear progression\n- **Registry entries** inserted alphabetically between \"spinner\"→\"switch\" and \"switch-demo\"→\"table-demo\"\n- **`lucide-react`** is the only dependency (for `CheckIcon`)",
